meanings.definition: To exceed in rate or amount.
meanings.sent1: The new car outrates the old one in speed.
meanings.sent2: Her dedication outrates her talent in achieving success.
meanings.sent3: The rabbit outrates the turtle in the race, surprising everyone.
meanings.sent4: His enthusiasm outrates his experience in the project.
meanings.sent5: The sun outrates the moon in brightness, lighting up the sky.

meanings.definition: To surpass in speed or efficiency.
meanings.sent1: The new technology outrates the old one in efficiency.
meanings.sent2: She outrates her colleagues in completing tasks quickly.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outrates the other animals in gathering nuts for winter.
meanings.sent4: His determination outrates his physical limitations in the race.
meanings.sent5: The cheetah outrates all other animals in speed, sprinting across the savannah.
